# Create, extract files

# Create:
tar -cvf file.tar /some/pathtar -cvJf file.tar.xz /some/pathtar -cvzf file.tar.gz /some/pathtar -cvjf file.tar.bz2 /some/path

# Extract:
tar -xvf file.tartar -xvJf file.tar.xztar -xvzf file.tar.gztar -xvjf file.tar.bz2tar -xvf file.tar -C /some/path # Untar to directory

# List contents:
tar -tf file.tartar -tvf file.tar # Like ls -l

# Options:

# - `-c` Create archive
# - `-x` Extract
# - `-t --list` List contents
# - `-f file` File name
# - `-v` Verbose (optional)
# - `-z` Compress using gzip
# - `-j` Compress using bz2 (better)

# More info:

# - Dash vs. no dash: <https://serverfault.com/a/474567>
# - <https://xkcd.com/1168/>

